Here’s a bash script that automates bug bounty recon and scanning, using the top 5 most-used tools:

⸻

🛠️ Tools Included:
	1.	subfinder – subdomain enumeration
	2.	httpx – live host probing
	3.	gau – gather URLs from Wayback/OTX
	4.	nuclei – vulnerability scanning
	5.	ffuf – directory fuzzing

⸻

📜 Script: bounty_hunter.sh

# -----------------------------
:
✅ To Use:
	1.	Install the tools (see below)
	2.	Save the script as bounty_hunter.sh
	3.	Make it executable:

chmod +x bounty_hunter.sh


	 4.	Run it:

./bounty_hunter.sh target.com



⸻

🧱 Install Tools (One-liners):

# Install subfinder
go install -v github.com/projectdiscovery/subfinder/v2/cmd/subfinder@latest

# Install httpx
go install -v github.com/projectdiscovery/httpx/cmd/httpx@latest

# Install gau
go install github.com/lc/gau/v2/cmd/gau@latest

# Install nuclei
go install -v github.com/projectdiscovery/nuclei/v3/cmd/nuclei@latest

# Install ffuf
go install github.com/ffuf/ffuf/v2@latest

Also install SecLists for wordlists.

⸻

